                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Over the course of the past week, several banks in Pennsylvania's "Oil
                    Region" went under, causing considerable "excitement" in business circles
                    throughout the state. Included among the list is the Venango Bank, of Franklin
                    county, whose notes, the article reports, will no longer be accepted as tender.</summary>
